  "text": "Even though the correlational analysis revealed significant relationships between problem-focused, emotion-focused and maladaptive coping, only the latter was significant in explaining the variance of adjustment to disability. Contrary to earlier findings [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] where both problem and emotion-focused coping strategies were associated with better mental health and higher quality of life, we did not find problem-focused and emotion-focused coping strategies to be significant predictors of adjustment. Meanwhile, frequent use of maladaptive coping strategies contributed to high levels of depression and this can negatively impact adjustment to disability (Ziarko, Mojs, Piasecki, & Samborski, 2014) .",
